			<p>The site is a light-weight <a href="http://nodejs.org/">node.js</a> front-end to <a href="http://flickr.com/photos/boise">Flickr</a> hosted at <a href="https://www.heroku.com/">Heroku</a> with a caching layer at <a href="http://redis-cloud.com/">Redis Cloud</a>. The writing is embedded in the images as captions which come through the <a href="http://www.flickr.com/services/api/">Flickr API</a> and some regex to make it pretty.</p>
			<p>The map overview and links are generated automatically from the coordinates also embedded in the images. Basically, I press the &ldquo;<a href="http://regex.info/blog/lightroom-goodies/flickr">publish</a>&rdquo; button in <a href="http://www.adobe.com/products/photoshop-lightroom.html">Lightroom</a> and the stuff appears here, nice and neat.</p>
